					<em><figcaption>Iconic Spitfire planes during the Battle of Britain</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today United Kingdom is still a unitary parliamentary and a constitutional monarchy. It remains a global power in economic, cultural, scientific and military influence. The UK is a leading member NATO, World Trade Organisation. The UK was a member of the European Union and its predecessor the EEC for 47 years, however they opted to withdraw in January 2020.
			</p>
		</div>
		
	
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically England accounts for 50% of land mass in the UK. Mostly consists of lowlands. City of London lies around the Thames river. Beyond this
bustling capital are rocky shores along the coastline, bustling cities of Liverpool, Manchester and Birmingham, and the moors and lakes in the North. The highest point in England is Scafell Pike at 978 meters high(3,200feet).
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.wedreamoftravel.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/The-White-Cliffs-of-Dover-4.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>White cliffs of Dover, Southern England</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Scotland accounts for 32% of the UK land, and consists of 800 islands. Scotland is the most mountainous part of the UK with Ben Nevis, the highest mountain at 1,345 meters (4,400 feet). Most of the people live in the city of Glasgow and the capital Edinburgh.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://i.assetzen.net/i/CgjTKa70V4M0/w:1200/h:/q:70.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
