				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Wales accounts for 10% of the land mass of the UK. Wales also is mountainous with Snowdon at 1,085 meters high (3,500 feet). Most of the population live in the coastal cities of Cardiff, Swansea and Newport.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Northern Ireland is on an island separated from the Great Britain. Northern Ireland borders Republic of Ireland to the south and Irish Sea and North Sea to the North. Most of Northern Ireland is hilly. Mourne Mountains are the highest point with 850 meters high(2,795 feet). Belfast, a major sea port, is the biggest city, and the capital of Northern Ireland.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
