				Climate in the UK and Northern Ireland is oceanic and generally rainy, mild with not too many temperature fluctuations. Temperatures in the winter are around 5 to 8 degrees celsius (40-45 degree fahrenheit), and in summers are 14 to 16
degrees celsius (55-60 degree Fahrenheit). Northern Scotland is the coolest part of the UK with heavy snowfall in the mountains.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
