				The most famous cruise ship RMS Titanic was designed by an Irish architect Thomas Andrews, and was built in Belfast’s shipping port. Titanic sunk hitting a massive iceberg in the middle of the ocean on April 15, 1912 killing 1500 passengers and crew.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
	
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
