				In the town of Ballymoney there is a road called the Dark Hedges. It is a road surrounded by nearly 300 year old beech trees. The trees were planted by James Stuart the owner of the land in 1743, and the mansion on the nearby property GraceHill. The mansion is now a part of the golf club and the Dark Hedges are one of Ireland’s most striking natural landmarks visited by many people. The road of these massive trees is supposed to be haunted by a “Gray Lady” ghost who appears to travelers at dusk.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
